ting figure in this study is Peter the Venerable, one of Europe's leading intellectuals and abbot of Cluny from 1122 to 1156, who commissioned Latin translations of Muslim texts such as the Qur'an. Cluny and the Muslims of La Garde-Freinet provides us with an unparalleled opportunity to examine Christian perceptions of Islam in the Crusading era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChristian hagiographyxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aChristianity and other religionsxIslamxEarly works to 1800. 0aIslamxControversial literaturexEarly works to 1800. 0aIslamxRelationsxChristianityxEarly works to 1800. 0aMuslimszFrancezLa Garde-FreinetxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aIslamic Religion & Studies. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aReligious Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aMonks, Cluny, Islam, Religious Conversion, Hagiography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170092740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501700927423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501700927/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles